Tom.</VOLUME> <FORMAT>fol.</FORMAT> <YEAR>1741</YEAR>; davon die 3. ersten Tom. dato schon zu beziehen sind; das gantze Werck kostet samt der Fracht <PRIZE>fl. 24</PRIZE></BIBL>. <BIBL><TITLE>Dictionaire Oeconomique, continant les moyens d'Augmenter son dien & de conserver sa sante</TITLE>, par <AUTHOR>Mister Noel Chomel</AUTHOR>, Augmente dun Nouveau Supplement de deur Volumes, par <AUTHOR>F. So dann sind bey ihnen auch genugsam annoch zu haben: <BIBL><TITLE>Dictionaire Historique & Critique de Mr. Bayle</TITLE>- <VOLUME>4. Specifically:
1. \u221a\u00a7den -> läden (Buchläden)
2. B\u221a\u00bacher -> Bücher
3. appell\u221a\u00a9 -> appelé
4. di\u221a\u00fc -> diü
5. \u221a\u2020 (used before PRIZE/PRICE) removed as it seems to be an artifact/separator that doesn't belong in the structure.

8. I standardized the closing characters for the price tags where \u221a\u2020 was present before them, removing the artifact."}
